
n.n.n / 2010-10-02 
==================

  * Header rewrite
  * Correct minor bug on icon set for the SSH protocol + finalize POD document (Authors/copyright etc.)
  * Minor correction on icon path to work on Ubuntu
  * Correct last mispellings after iBackup -> yaBackup renaming (especially in the 'make check' tests)
  * Finish (hopefully) the complete renaming of the script (together with the dependencies) from ibackup to yaBackup
  * icon renaming ibackup -> yabackup
  * finalize POD doc
  * Correct CSS
  * continue on POD documentation
  * Start POD documentation
  * New icons files added
  * Correct path management in src_rootdir and finalize sparsebundel support
  * Update checking of used modules
  * Add function to the bootstrap script to extract the used Perl modules
  * 
  * Add a new tests/ directory containing the regression tests generated using the modules Test::More and Test::Cmd
  * Add a new tests directory for regression tests based on Test::More and Test::Cmd
  * Correct error in unmount when dealing with encfs+ssh and spaces in the directory of the mounted dir
  * Work against spaces in filenames that appear to be a nightmare for rsync over SSH (but not only)
  * FInalize tests for protocols file, drive, ssh and there respective encfs versions
  * Finalize select_element over SSH (better find command)
  * - Add new function for execute with collection of the outpu - better handling of sync::select_element() to list elements over SSH in case of restoration
  * Update SSH icon (both encrypted and normal version to make 'SSH' more visible
  * Rename the icon files to facilitate the access using $BACKUP_CMD_INFO{'proto'}
  * Add icons folder
  * Add separate icones
  * Add remote encfs volume mount/umount Add execute_and_set_stdin
  * Continue on EncFS port
  * Start adding EncFS support
  * Add sync package
  * continue on integration
  * Add exception mechnanism via Exception::Class. Note: install v.1.30 until 1.31 correct the bug on circular dependencies upon cpan install
  * Start refactoring the code into packages
  * Creating a private branch of ibackup/calc for the code splitting via packages
  * Add link to LBackup
  * Update the website for the release

